s every hour using a time-weighted average price (TWAP) mechanism comparing the perpetual price to the oracle-fed spot price. The vAMM (virtual Automated Market Maker) combined with the DLOB (Decentralized Limit Order Book) ensures tight spreads and efficient funding rate calculations. JIT (Just-in-Time) liquidity auctions provide additional liquidity during volatile periods, affecting funding rate dynamics. Insurance fund contributions help stabilize rates during extreme market conditions."}]]}],"$Lf",["$L10","$L11","$L12"],"$L13"]}],"$L14"]}]]}]
